name: integer_i32_binary32_first_lost_negative
description: |
  This is -(2^24 + 1), the first negative integer by magnitude that does not
  survive conversion to binary32 and back. Round-to-nearest maps it to -2^24,
  checking that signed conversion loses precision symmetrically.
format: hex
decode-as: i32
pair:
  - with: ../u32/binary32-first-lost-integer.input
    hint: tricky
tags:
  - "integer"
  - "signed-integer"
  - "i32"
  - "binary32"
  - "float-roundtrip"
  - "negative"
  - "precision-loss"
  - "boundary"
---
ff ff ff fe   # -16777217 (-(2^24 + 1))
